cs.DB, cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper primarily focuses on improving the performance of in-memory databases, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Database). It also discusses the implementation of hardware transactional memory in IBM Power architectures, which falls under the category of cs.AR (Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes a software layer to improve the performance of HTM, which falls under the category of cs.OS (Operating Systems) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of SI-HTM on benchmarks, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
